Each node can have maximum two children.
Binary Search Tree - A node's left child must have a value less than its parent
A node's right child must have a value greater than or equal to its parent
common operations
find, insert, traverse, delete
When the data items that need to be arranged in a tree arrive in an ascending or
descending order, tree becomes unbalanced and its efficiency may be seriously degraded.


implement Huffman Encoding using priority queue and binary tree